---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = '23 April 2026';
---

<Layout
  title="Terms of Service | Beyond Border Group"
  description="Terms governing the use of Beyond Border Group's website and services. Client responsibilities, payment terms, liability, and governing law."
>
  <section class="legal-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="eyebrow">Legal</span>
      <h1 class="legal-hero__title">Terms of Service</h1>
      <p class="legal-hero__meta">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>
      <p class="legal-hero__lead">
        Beyond Border Group is operated by BeyondBorderGroup LTD, a Hong Kong SAR registered
        entity. By accessing our website or engaging our services, you agree to these Terms of
        Service. If you do not agree, please do not use the website or our services.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section legal-body">
    <div class="container">
      <article class="prose">
        <h2>Services</h2>
        <p>
          Beyond Border Group provides marketing, eCommerce and distribution services focused on
          the Chinese market. These include, without limitation, market entry consulting,
          cross-border eCommerce setup and operations, social commerce, content creation,
          advertising, influencer campaigns, and distribution into Chinese retail. Specific
          deliverables for each engagement are defined in an individual client agreement or
          statement of work.
        </p>

        <h2>Website use</h2>
        <p>
          When using our website, you agree not to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Engage in any unlawful activity</li>
          <li>Transmit spam or unsolicited messages</li>
          <li>Attempt to gain unauthorised access to our systems or networks</li>
          <li>Scrape or harvest data from the site without our written permission</li>
          <li>Interfere with the operation, security or integrity of the website</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Intellectual property</h2>
        <p>
          All content on this website, including text, graphics, logos, images, and code, is
          the property of Beyond Border Group unless otherwise indicated, and is protected by
          applicable intellectual property laws. Client work product transfers to the client
          upon full payment of all applicable fees, unless otherwise specified in the client
          agreement.
        </p>

        <h2>Client responsibilities</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Provide accurate and complete information to enable us to deliver the services</li>
          <li>Review and approve deliverables within the timeframes agreed</li>
          <li>Ensure that any materials supplied to us do not infringe third-party rights</li>
          <li>Pay agreed fees on schedule</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Payment terms</h2>
        <p>
          Unless otherwise specified in a client agreement, fees are billed monthly in advance.
          Late payments may accrue interest at 1.5% per month. We reserve the right to suspend
          services if payment is more than 15 days overdue.
        </p>

        <h2>Confidentiality</h2>
        <p>
          Each party agrees to protect the confidential information of the other party shared
          during the engagement, and to maintain that confidentiality for a period of two years
          following the end of the engagement.
        </p>

        <h2>Limitation of liability</h2>
        <p>
          Our services are provided "as is" without warranties of any kind, express or implied.
          To the maximum extent permitted by law, our total liability for any claim arising out
          of or related to a service is limited to the fees paid by the client for that specific
          service.
        </p>

        <h2>Indemnification</h2>
        <p>
          The client agrees to defend, indemnify and hold harmless Beyond Border Group against
          any claims, damages or expenses arising from the client's misuse of the website, breach
          of these terms, or infringement of third-party rights.
        </p>

        <h2>Termination</h2>
        <p>
          Either party may end an engagement by written notice in accordance with the terms of
          the applicable client agreement. Beyond Border Group reserves the right to suspend or
          terminate a client's access to the website or services in the event of a material
          breach of these terms.
        </p>

        <h2>Governing law</h2>
        <p>
          These Terms of Service are governed by the laws of the Hong Kong Special Administrative
          Region. Any dispute arising out of or in connection with these terms is subject to the
          exclusive jurisdiction of the Hong Kong courts.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes to terms</h2>
        <p>
          We may update these Terms of Service from time to time. Any changes take effect when
          posted on this page. Your continued use of our website or services constitutes
          acceptance of the revised terms.
        </p>

        <h2>Severability</h2>
        <p>
          If any provision of these terms is held to be invalid or unenforceable, the remaining
          provisions continue in full force and effect.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          If you have questions about these Terms of Service, email
          <a href="mailto:hello@beyondbordergroup.com">hello@beyondbordergroup.com</a>
          or use our <a href="/contact">contact page</a>.
        </p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

<style>
  .legal-hero {
    background: var(--bbg-surface);
    padding: var(--space-7) 0 var(--space-6);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--bbg-border);
  }
  .legal-hero .container > * { max-width: 760px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; }
  .legal-hero__title {
    font-size: clamp(2.25rem, 4vw + 1rem, 3.5rem);
    font-weight: 700;
    line-height: 1.1;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--bbg-ink);
    margin: var(--space-3) auto var(--space-3);
  }
  .legal-hero__meta {
    font-size: var(--fs-small);
    color: var(--bbg-text-muted);
    margin: 0 auto var(--space-5);
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }
  .legal-hero__lead {
    font-size: var(--fs-lead);
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--bbg-text);
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
  }

  .legal-body { padding-top: var(--space-7); padding-bottom: var(--space-7); }

  .prose {
    max-width: 760px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    color: var(--bbg-text);
    font-size: var(--fs-body);
    line-height: 1.7;
  }
  .prose h2 {
    font-size: 1.5rem;
    font-weight: 700;
    color: var(--bbg-ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
    margin: var(--space-7) 0 var(--space-3);
    line-height: 1.25;
  }
  .prose h2:first-child { margin-top: 0; }
  .prose h3 {
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    font-weight: 600;
    color: var(--bbg-ink);
    margin: var(--space-5) 0 var(--space-2);
    line-height: 1.3;
  }
  .prose p { margin: 0 0 var(--space-4); }
  .prose ul {
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
    margin: 0 0 var(--space-4);
  }
  .prose li { margin-bottom: var(--space-2); }
  .prose a { color: var(--bbg-blue); text-decoration: underline; text-underline-offset: 3px; }
  .prose a:hover { color: var(--bbg-blue-dark); }
</style>
